sentences: In 2006, he recorded his Start Something EP by himself on his 16-track recorder.
The single "Lost My Soul" polled at number 26 in NME's Top 50 singles of 2006.
On 19 May 2007, his debut studio album We Can Create was released on Mute Records.
His first North American release, To the Sky EP, was digitally released on 22 May on the same label.
On 17 July, it was announced that We Can Create had been nominated for the Mercury Music Prize.
However, it lost out to Klaxons' debut album Myths of the Near Future.
On 22 February 2009, James wrote on his MySpace blog about his new upcoming album, saying "I've never been more confident and excited about this new album".
Turning the Mind was released on 28 September 2009 in Europe, and 20 October in North America.

Maps' third album, titled Vicissitude, was released on Mute on 8 July 2013.
A compilation album of remixes, titled Realigned, was released on Mute on 15 August 2014.
In 2016 Chapman collaborated with Mute Records label mate Polly Scattergood, under the name onDeadWaves.

Maps returned to the live arena that same year to promote the album with a full live band, for a number of shows in the U.K., including a sold out show at The Purcell Room, Southbank Centre in July 2019.
